npc/nadia: You made it through. But you're not in the city anymore.
npc/nadia: This is the first layer of the internet — the public web. The surface.
npc/nadia: Out there it looks like a screen full of apps and bright promises. In here, you see it for what it is.
npc/nadia: Those swarming things? Adbots — spam given a body. Built from the gambling ads that started this crisis. Same flashing psychology, multiplied across millions of phones.
npc/nadia: And here's the promise they all lead with: "free credit," "bonus," "guaranteed jackpot."
npc/nadia: Ask one question and the whole trap falls apart — if the money really flowed TO the players, who would pay for all these apps, these ads, these towers?
npc/nadia: It flows the other way. Always. What you're handed for free is only bait to make you spend what isn't.
npc/nadia: Watch the platforms here. Some glitter with easy coins — a free foothold right where you want one. Step on, grab the coin, and it bites: slows you, drains you, or flips your controls.
npc/nadia: That is exactly how they got me. "Just claim your free credit." I claimed it. Then the next, and the next, until my rent money was gone and I was still chasing the first free thing.
npc/nadia: Nothing here is free. If a platform looks too generous, it is not a gift. It is bait.
